C'mon, let's go do something.

05:13.955 --> 05:15.081
All right.
All right.

05:15.165 --> 05:16.416
Go ahead.

05:16.499 --> 05:18.209
Go have fun, but stay out of
trouble, all right?

05:18.293 --> 05:24.090
- Yes, sir.
- All right?

05:24.174 --> 05:26.217
They're boys, Ma.

05:26.301 --> 05:27.469
My goodness.

05:27.552 --> 05:29.929
I know, but I worry
so about Will.

05:30.013 --> 05:31.556
You gotta let him be
a boy.

05:31.639 --> 05:32.891
You
can't keep him on the farm

05:32.974 --> 05:34.434
forever, honey. Come
on.

05:34.517 --> 05:35.894
Well, what are we
gonna do?

05:35.977 --> 05:37.729
We take him into town and
everybody laughs at him.

05:37.812 --> 05:38.730
Ah.

05:38.813 --> 05:39.648
They laugh at all
of us.

05:39.731 --> 05:40.565
You don't mind those
people.

05:40.649 --> 05:42.067
That's just them being ignorant.

05:42.150 --> 05:44.235
What about them
fighting with

05:44.319 --> 05:45.320
the other boys?

05:45.403 --> 05:47.072
You know, I'll sit 'em
down,

05:47.155 --> 05:49.908
I'll remind 'em that fighting is
never the answer.

05:49.991 --> 05:53.411
Okay? Come on.

05:53.495 --> 05:55.246
Well, what about
his schooling?

05:55.330 --> 05:56.748
You know, how is he ever going
to get

05:56.831 --> 05:58.917
an education if the school
doesn't even want him to attend?

05:59.501 --> 06:01.252
Well, why don't we go
check out

06:01.336 --> 06:03.630
that school in Columbus that the
doc told us about?

06:03.713 --> 06:06.675
He'll be with... he'll be with
other kids just like him.

06:07.342 --> 06:08.927
But it's so far.

06:09.010 --> 06:12.263
Well, we'll go look
at it.

06:12.347 --> 06:13.765
What do
you say?

06:13.848 --> 06:16.267
Come on, now.

