give that a thought.
Good to see you.

24:53.134 --> 24:58.223
Hey, what's wrong,
son?

24:58.306 --> 24:59.683
You okay?

25:03.311 --> 25:07.565
Oh.
Am I ashamed of you?

25:07.649 --> 25:14.739
Oh, no.
What made you think a thing like

25:14.823 --> 25:15.907
that?

25:15.991 --> 25:19.619
You read their lips and they
said

25:19.703 --> 25:22.914
they don't want you in town?

25:22.998 --> 25:27.919
Listen to me. To hell with them.
Just to hell with them.

25:28.003 --> 25:30.755
You just keep doin' you a fine
job and

25:30.839 --> 25:32.257
they'll come back.

25:32.340 --> 25:34.592
You believe me, I know.
And you can

25:34.676 --> 25:36.594
start with that pair of boots.

25:36.678 --> 25:37.971
Give me that here.

25:38.054 --> 25:41.850
Just to hell with 'em.
You do your work, they'll come.

25:59.868 --> 26:06.458
That's a fine piece of work.

26:06.541 --> 26:08.960
Oh, hello, Miss. Can I help you?

26:09.044 --> 26:11.463
I'd like to know,
sir, how much it

26:11.546 --> 26:13.506
would cost to get these shoes
fixed up.

26:13.590 --> 26:16.468
I'll take a look at
'em.

26:16.551 --> 26:18.970
Oh, Miss, I'm afraid these...

26:19.054 --> 26:23.933
these shoes are beyond repair.
Would you like to

26:24.017 --> 26:25.894
buy another pair?

26:26.770 --> 26:28.980
No, I... I can't.

26:29.064 --> 26:31.358
All right.
Well, I thank you for

26:31.441 --> 26:33.318
coming in and I wish you good
day.

26:33.401 --> 26:35.278
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

26:52.587 --> 26:54.339
Damn, would ya
look at these?

26:54.422 --> 26:55.840
I'd swear these here are new
shoes.

26:55.924 --> 27:00.011
Did you do this
work, boy?

27:00.095 --> 27:02.514
Ain't no damn
way.

27:02.597 --> 27:06.685
Well, iffin' he
did, he's the best.

27:06.768 --> 27:08.019
Except for you, Dave.

27:08.103 --> 27:10.188
Yeah, you're the
best.

27:10.271 --> 27:13.233
I know that, boys.
He's a fine cobbler.

27:13.316 --> 27:15.860
Well, we'll be
gettin' on now.

27:15.944 --> 27:16.903
See you, Dave.

27:16.987 --> 27:18.697
Yeah, see 'ya,
Dave.

27:18.780 --> 27:20.865
We'll tell everybody he's real
good.

27:20.949 --> 27:23.034
Thanks, Dummy.

27:23.118 --> 27:30.792
Hey!
His name is William.

27:43.638 --> 27:47.058
Oh, well, we should
have these

27:47.142 --> 27:50.562
ready in about... oh, about a
week, boys.

27:50.645 --> 27:54.149
Here you go.
There you go.

27:59.154 --> 28:01.573
Oh, Ruth, there.
Mabel.

28:01.656 --> 28:05.910
Let me see what you got here.
Oh, dear.

28:05.994 --> 28:08.246
Why did you wait so long before
you brought

28:08.330 --> 28:09.789
your shoes in to be fixed?

28:09.873 --> 28:10.749
Well... well, we
we didn't. It's just that...

28:11.833 --> 28:12.959
We didn't have the
time.

28:13.043 --> 28:14.127
That's it.
That's what it was.

28:14.210 --> 28:15.545
Oh, well, that's
all right.

28:15.628 --> 28:18.798
We're gonna fix these shoes so
they look brand-new, huh?

28:18.882 --> 28:21.760
TWill they be as
good as the Waller boys' shoes?

28:21.843 --> 28:24.262
Even better.

28:24.346 --> 28:25.347
Thank you, Mr.
Beagle.

28:25.430 --> 28:26.264
Yes, thank you.

28:26.348 --> 28:28.058
Take care.

28:33.521 --> 28:35.690
How would you like
to buy the shop?

28:44.407 --> 28:45.325
Yeah.
Yeah.

28:45.408 --> 28:47.952
Well, you know, I'm gettin' up
in

28:48.036 --> 28:51.122
years, and, well, my hands, you
know,

28:51.206 --> 28:55.627
they're just... they're no good
anymore,

28:55.710 --> 28:59.798
and this town needs a good
cobbler,

28:59.881 --> 29:06.596
and I can't think of anybody
better than you. Huh? What?

29:11.226 --> 29:13.645
Oh, yeah, you gotta talk to your
dad.

29:13.728 --> 29:17.232
You talk to your dad and you
let me know what he says.

29:17.315 --> 29:18.316
All right?

29:18.400 --> 29:22.070
Now let's get back and do this
work.

29:42.924 --> 29:43.925
Oh, look, there's that
dummy.

29:44.926 --> 29:49.597
- Ow, Ma!
- Ow!

29:57.272 --> 30:01.109
Daddy, come on.
This way.

30:03.778 --> 30:06.865
Preacher, great
sermon.

30:06.948 --> 30:07.907
Thank you.

30:22.672 --> 30:27.135
Who's that?

30:28.011 --> 30:30.513
Well, I know it's a
girl.

30:32.474 --> 30:33.475
She came in the shop

30:33.558 --> 30:36.061
the other day
needing some shoes.

30:36.519 --> 30:42.233
Well, she's pretty.
Do you like her a little bit?

30:42.317 --> 30:46.571
Huh? Easy, boys.
Come on, now.

30:46.655 --> 30:50.241
She is pretty, though.

30:50.325 --> 30:53.328
Hey, how's...
how's Mr. Beagle treating you?

30:59.709 --> 31:02.754
Real fine, Pop.
It's pretty busy now.

31:02.837 --> 31:06.925
Mister... Mr. Beagle
wants to sell you the shop?

31:07.008 --> 31:09.594
That's great news, son.
That is great.

31:09.678 --> 31:15.934
That's wonderful. Wow.
I'm proud of you.

31:16.017 --> 31:18.603
Wait.
You've earned it.

31:18.687 --> 31:20.647
It's good.
You've earned it.

31:20.730 --> 31:22.440
You keep it up.
Okay?

31:22.524 --> 31:27.070
I'm proud of you. Uh-huh.

32:08.403 --> 32:11.323
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa!

32:11.406 --> 32:14.200
Sir, I can't pay for these.
I got no money.

32:14.284 --> 32:16.995
Didn't you hear what I said?

32:17.078 --> 32:19.581
I got no money.

32:21.583 --> 32:28.256
For me?
Thanks, sir. Oh!

32:36.431 --> 32:37.682
Look, guys,
look!

32:37.766 --> 32:39.184
Look what the new cobbler gave
me!

32:39.267 --> 32:41.144
Woah!

32:43.605 --> 32:47.859
You're a good man,
William.

32:47.942 --> 32:49.778
A very fine man.

32:52.781 --> 32:55.533
Hi.
I know you can't

32:55.617 --> 32:58.036
hear me, but I wanted to say

32:58.119 --> 33:02.374
thank you for giving my brother
shoes.

33:02.457 --> 33:05.877
I'd like to pay you for them.

33:05.960 --> 33:09.547
I know it's not much,
but it's all I have.

33:09.631 --> 33:17.013
My pa, he doesn't work much.
I'm sorry. Oh.

33:23.311 --> 33:30.694
You're very kind. Thank you.

33:46.501 --> 33:53.883
Hi, William Hoy.
I'm Sarah Evans.

34:24.205 --> 34:28.375
Yes, I'm fine,
thank you.

34:32.880 --> 34:37.009
Are you waiting for
someone?

34:37.092 --> 34:40.471
Yes, I am waiting for someone.

34:40.554 --> 34:47.895
No, I'm waiting for you. You.
Do you want to walk?

35:06.748 --> 35:09.501
I want you to teach
me

35:09.584 --> 35:11.836
how to talk with my hands.

35:11.920 --> 35:18.134
You want to learn sign?

35:26.601 --> 35:28.687
You want
to learn how to sign?

35:28.770 --> 35:33.775
Yes. Yes, I want to learn.

35:52.794 --> 35:56.214
Excuse me.
Excuse me.

35:56.297 --> 35:58.758
I need my shoes fixed.

35:58.842 --> 36:03.555
Hey, buddy, you gonna answer me?
Hey!

36:03.638 --> 36:06.391
Hey!

36:06.474 --> 36:09.769
Okay, then.

36:09.853 --> 36:16.109
I'll go someplace else.

36:16.192 --> 36:18.486
Finally I get your
attention.

36:20.530 --> 36:24.284
You can't hear?

36:24.367 --> 36:27.412
Well, why don't you rig you up
somethin' to this door,

36:27.495 --> 36:31.750
a pulley system, so when you
open the door...

36:31.833 --> 36:35.587
... it
falls.

36:35.670 --> 36:41.301
Look, here's the door.

36:41.384 --> 36:45.930
You get a pulley, take
a line, and

36:46.014 --> 36:50.101
you rig it, you tie it to this
hammer.

36:50.185 --> 36:57.484
When the door opens, the hammer
falls

36:57.567 --> 37:00.945
and you feel it.

37:01.029 --> 37:05.617
You're welcome.

37:05.700 --> 37:08.453
I need new soles.

37:08.536 --> 37:10.955
I'll fix them for free.

37:11.039 --> 37:13.124
Oh, no, no, no, no.
You work

37:13.208 --> 37:14.626
really hard.
I'll pay you.

37:14.709 --> 37:15.710
I'll pay you.

37:15.794 --> 37:19.130
I want to
pay you

37:19.214 --> 37:21.007
back for your idea.

37:21.091 --> 37:25.303
Just do a really good
job on them.

37:25.387 --> 37:28.056
That'll be payment enough.

37:30.892 --> 37:32.143
That's good.

37:32.227 --> 37:33.895
Good.
Thank you very much.

37:52.414 --> 37:57.335
Throw it! Throw it!

37:57.419 --> 38:00.672
He's out. He's out!
You see that throw?

38:00.755 --> 38:03.508
That's no fair.
He can't do that.

38:03.591 --> 38:05.260
He ain't even playin'.

38:25.280 --> 38:29.784
Why you got that
hammer hittin' the floor?

38:30.618 --> 38:31.703
Come
here.

38:31.786 --> 38:32.829
Put your hands on the floor.

38:39.627 --> 38:41.296
The floor
vibrates.

38:51.139 --> 38:53.058
What does it say?

38:53.141 --> 39:00.148
Si-si-since I cannot
h-h-hear, I f-f-

39:02.317 --> 39:08.239
feel the... the vibr-bration.

39:08.323 --> 39:10.950
He feels the vibration.
That's what it says.

39:11.034 --> 39:12.035
Why can't you hear?

39:12.118 --> 39:13.411
He can't
hear you, stupid.

39:13.828 --> 39:15.455
Don't call me stupid.

39:15.538 --> 39:16.748
He just told you he
can't hear,

39:16.831 --> 39:17.999
so why did you ask the question?

39:18.083 --> 39:19.584
- Then write it.
- You write it.

39:19.668 --> 39:21.252
Why?
'Cause you can't write, stupid?

39:21.336 --> 39:22.420
- Can you?
- Yeah.

39:22.504 --> 39:24.255
Okay.
Then go ahead, write it.

39:24.339 --> 39:25.590
Why don't you-all write
it?

39:25.674 --> 39:27.092
Well, you asked the
question.

39:27.175 --> 39:29.469
Yeah, you asked the
question.

39:29.552 --> 39:31.596
Calm
down.

39:31.680 --> 39:35.100
Would you like to
play baseball with us?

39:35.183 --> 39:38.269
Baseball.

39:38.353 --> 39:41.272
Would you like to play with us?

39:41.356 --> 39:45.360
If you
learn to

39:49.698 --> 39:57.205
read and write, we can play
baseball.

40:15.765 --> 40:17.726
Let me
have it.

40:35.410 --> 40:37.996
Let's
play.

41:28.797 --> 41:33.218
Gene was the
kindest little

41:33.301 --> 41:37.847
soul in the world, but this hint
about...

41:44.980 --> 41:52.737
I want to see you.

42:11.006 --> 42:15.802
You... you want to
start a team

42:15.885 --> 42:17.429
with us?
Wow!

42:17.512 --> 42:19.180
Ya mean it?

42:33.695 --> 42:40.368
How do you always know
where the ball is going?

42:48.043 --> 42:53.465
Wow!

42:59.054 --> 43:02.307
Excuse me, boys.
What's the name of your team?

43:02.390 --> 43:05.185
Stonewall Jackson Ball
Club.

43:05.268 --> 43:08.146
That's a great name.
Play here every day?

43:08.229 --> 43:10.649
That's right, Mister.
That's our playing field.

43:10.732 --> 43:12.192
Yeah, we got us a big
game

43:12.275 --> 43:13.485
tomorrow over at the park.

43:13.568 --> 43:15.487
Yeah, it's gonna be big.
The whole

43:15.570 --> 43:17.489
darn town's gonna come out and
watch us.

43:17.572 --> 43:19.157
That's great.

43:19.240 --> 43:23.495
Tell me somethin', that guy with
the shirt and the tie, who's he?

43:23.578 --> 43:27.666
He's the cobbler.
He play pretty good, don't he?

43:27.749 --> 43:30.001
Yes, he does.

43:30.085 --> 43:33.546
Okay.
Yeah, we won't tell Pa

43:33.630 --> 43:35.507
we're playing ball.

43:35.590 --> 43:38.510
Thank you, boys.
Good luck tomorrow.

43:38.593 --> 43:44.516
- Thanks, Mister.
- You bet.

43:44.599 --> 43:49.229
Young man,
can I have a moment?

43:49.312 --> 43:55.360
Excuse me. Young man. Excuse me.

43:58.947 --> 44:02.200
Excuse me. Young man.

44:02.283 --> 44:03.118
Hey, Mister,

44:03.201 --> 44:07.038
you know he can't hear 'ya,
don't 'ya?

44:07.122 --> 44:08.081
Who?

44:08.164 --> 44:10.208
The cobbler, Dummy
Hoy.

44:10.291 --> 44:12.252
Why do you call him
that?

44:12.335 --> 44:16.047
Because he's deaf
and dumb.

44:16.131 --> 44:17.382
You're talkin' about the
young man

44:17.465 --> 44:19.009
that just walked into that shoe
store?

44:19.092 --> 44:21.344
Yes, sir.

44:21.428 --> 44:22.887
That's exactly who
I'm talking about.

44:23.513 --> 44:24.764
Can't hear anything?

44:24.848 --> 44:27.267
Poor boy can't
hear or speak a lick.

44:27.350 --> 44:28.810
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

44:30.312 --> 44:36.818
Ball. Ball.
B-A-L-L.

44:50.165 --> 44:53.084
What's with you
and that deaf and dumb boy?

44:53.168 --> 44:55.962
Nothing, Daddy.
He's just a nice boy.

44:56.046 --> 44:57.756
Yeah.
Well, you two

44:57.839 --> 44:59.299
seem to be gettin' real close.

44:59.382 --> 45:02.093
Daddy, I like him.

45:02.177 --> 45:06.306
He's not normal.
I don't want you gettin' to like

45:06.389 --> 45:07.265
him too much.

45:07.349 --> 45:09.934
Now, what's all this hand stuff?

45:10.018 --> 45:11.770
That's the way he
talks.

45:11.853 --> 45:13.605
It makes the two
of you

45:13.688 --> 45:15.482
look like monkeys.
Stay away from him.

45:15.565 --> 45:16.566
Daddy!

45:16.650 --> 45:18.109
Did you
hear what I said?!

45:18.193 --> 45:20.111
He gave Jimmy a
pair of

45:20.195 --> 45:21.946
shoes whenever he needed them.

45:22.030 --> 45:23.782
If I hada known
he needed

45:23.865 --> 45:25.784
them, I would have got Jimmy
some shoes.

45:25.867 --> 45:27.619
Well, if you'd quit
drinking,

45:27.702 --> 45:28.995
you would have known.

45:29.079 --> 45:33.458
Woman,
talk some sense into this girl.

45:33.541 --> 45:35.877
Never mind.
I know what you're gonna say,

45:35.960 --> 45:36.795
Mama.

45:41.383 --> 45:43.968
Gittup here.
Gittup here.

45:44.052 --> 45:45.470
Whoa, boy.
Good boy.

45:45.553 --> 45:47.055
Let's go on.

45:47.138 --> 45:49.766
- Is that William and the boys?
- I believe it is.

45:50.767 --> 45:52.018
Frank!

45:52.102 --> 45:53.979
- Hey, Pa.
- Frank, come here.

45:54.062 --> 45:57.315
- What are you boys doin'?
- Nothing, Pa.

45:57.399 --> 45:58.650
Don't you "Nothing,
Pa" me.

45:58.733 --> 45:59.651
I saw you playing ball.

45:59.734 --> 46:01.820
William, I told you I didn't
want

46:01.903 --> 46:04.155
you playin' baseball, correct?

46:04.239 --> 46:05.824
Pa, William's real
good

46:05.907 --> 46:07.200
at playing baseball.

46:07.283 --> 46:08.493
Yeah, I don't want
to hear nothin' of it.

46:08.576 --> 46:11.329
You got a business to run right
now.

46:11.413 --> 46:12.998
Boys, get in the wagon.

46:13.081 --> 46:20.755
William, I want you back at the
shoe store.

46:39.774 --> 46:43.570
I'm sorry, I didn't mean
to...

46:43.653 --> 46:46.364
You played pretty good.

46:46.448 --> 46:52.704
You should be out there with
the rest of the boys having fun.

46:52.787 --> 46:54.289
You can't hear me, can you?

46:56.458 --> 46:58.209
I watched you play ball.

46:58.293 --> 47:00.962
You're a natural.

47:03.298 --> 47:06.801
Now, do you think you can play
that well against pro players?

47:08.803 --> 47:13.224
My name is Dooley.
I'm a baseball scout.

47:13.308 --> 47:19.064
I would like you to go to Urbana
with me

47:19.147 --> 47:23.902
and play for Kenton.
Can you go?

47:23.985 --> 47:25.987
Why?

47:38.041 --> 47:42.587
It doesn't look like there's a
lot of business.

47:42.671 --> 47:46.424
I'll tell you what, if you want
to go,

47:46.508 --> 47:50.261
be at the train station next
Saturday.

47:50.345 --> 47:53.181
I'll buy your ticket.

48:06.194 --> 48:08.947
Play that
one more

48:09.030 --> 48:10.615
time.
You sold that.

48:10.699 --> 48:12.784
Okay. Where is it now? Uh-huh.

48:12.867 --> 48:17.622
One more time.
One more time.

48:17.706 --> 48:20.625
Oh, hold on.
Let's see.

48:20.709 --> 48:23.128
This man saw me play
today and

48:23.211 --> 48:25.296
wants me to play on the Kenton
team.

48:25.380 --> 48:28.383
A man wants you to play baseball
for Kenton?

48:28.883 --> 48:30.885
Who is this man?

48:40.061 --> 48:42.522
His name is Dooley,
a baseball scout.

48:42.605 --> 48:46.651
Ora, give papa a kiss.
Go sit down, please.

48:46.735 --> 48:48.320
Thank you, Honey.

48:48.403 --> 48:52.490
William, we already talked about
baseball.

48:52.574 --> 48:54.576
You have a business now. Okay?

49:04.294 --> 49:05.670
It'll be for just one
day.

49:05.754 --> 49:08.506
Besides, no one is coming
into the shop right now.

49:08.590 --> 49:15.597
That's a bunch of hogwash.
Baseball is not a game for you.

49:20.935 --> 49:24.939
I'm good at it, Pa.
I said no.

49:31.279 --> 49:33.531
You said I could play.
I said maybe.

49:33.615 --> 49:39.204
He's real good, Pa.

49:39.287 --> 49:42.040
Anybody else?

49:42.123 --> 49:43.875
Listen to me, family,

49:43.958 --> 49:46.378
I don't think this is a good idea.

49:46.461 --> 49:50.465
He has a business now.
I'm sorry, son.

49:56.304 --> 49:59.641
Becca, that was a great dinner,
honey.

50:11.820 --> 50:16.282
Dummy, we heard about
the scout.

50:16.366 --> 50:20.203
Kenton and Urbana are big
rivals.

50:27.502 --> 50:34.759
What?

50:34.843 --> 50:40.682
This is your big chance.

51:00.076 --> 51:07.459
I think you
should follow your dream.

51:07.542 --> 51:12.464
My father would be very angry.

51:12.547 --> 51:17.635
Wouldn't he
want you to be happy?

51:17.719 --> 51:21.723
He wants
me to have a future. He's right.

51:27.062 --> 51:32.817
I know you want to
honor

51:32.901 --> 51:38.156
your father, but think about it.

51:38.239 --> 51:43.912
You are very good.

52:51.646 --> 52:53.481
Read it!

53:46.242 --> 53:49.245
All aboard!

53:56.252 --> 54:01.216
All aboard!

54:06.054 --> 54:10.517
Do you always wear a shirt and
tie?

54:10.600 --> 54:15.271
Get on the train.

54:45.969 --> 54:49.014
See that pitcher over
there?

54:49.097 --> 54:50.682
That's Billy Hart.

54:50.765 --> 54:54.311
Think you can hit off of him?

55:01.776 --> 55:07.532
Oh, yeah.
Don't let on that you're deaf.

55:07.615 --> 55:09.117
Trust me.

55:13.288 --> 55:16.333
Woah!

55:21.129 --> 55:22.422
Hey, Scout.

55:22.505 --> 55:25.717
Hello, boys.

55:25.800 --> 55:27.093
How ya doin', Scout?

55:27.177 --> 55:28.553
Good. Yourself, Billy?

55:28.636 --> 55:30.722
Feeling good.
Ready to beat your boys.

55:30.805 --> 55:31.931
Who 'ya got here?

55:32.015 --> 55:34.225
Oh, it's a new guy I'm
looking at.

55:34.309 --> 55:35.727
Wanna see him play.

55:35.810 --> 55:37.729
Your guys could use
all the help they can get.

55:37.812 --> 55:40.273
But he looks a little small
to be playing ball, ain't he?

55:40.357 --> 55:42.233
